1
00:00:10,875 --> 00:00:12,125
[elevator bell dings]

2
00:00:14,916 --> 00:00:17,583
Why the hell can't we go
all the way to the top?

3
00:00:17,666 --> 00:00:18,541
Ugh.

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,166
Well, this is gonna suck.

5
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:24,541
[whirring]

6
00:00:32,666 --> 00:00:35,166
-Looks like the gate is locked.
-Yeah?

7
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:38,083
And there's nothing in here
to help us get it open either.

8
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,666
Well, if you don't have
the answer,

9
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:42,000
then I sure as hell
don't know what to do.

10
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,750
I figured you'd say that.

11
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,458
I thought that you were supposed
to have a knack

12
00:00:45,541 --> 00:00:46,791
for this kinda stuff.

13
00:00:46,875 --> 00:00:48,500
Try somethin'!

14
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:49,583
Uh...

15
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:52,541
♪

16
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:00,333
Ugh.

17
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:02,416
You got anything useful
in that little bag of yours?

18
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:06,166
Don't be shy, what's in it?

19
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:14,333
A needle, some thread,
and something else.

20
00:01:14,416 --> 00:01:15,958
Hey, are you
one of those badasses

21
00:01:16,041 --> 00:01:18,291
who can pick a lock
with a needle?

22
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:19,333
[sighs]

23
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:21,958
No, I'm not.

24
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,375
And besides, even if I were,
there's no keyhole.

25
00:01:25,458 --> 00:01:28,458
Then what good is havin'
that kinda crap gonna do us?!

26
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:31,458
Move!

27
00:01:31,541 --> 00:01:33,083
I'll smash the door open!

28
00:01:34,291 --> 00:01:35,416
Those are iron bars.

29
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,166
Well, until you come up
with a better idea,

30
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:39,541
I'm gonna try things my way.

31
00:01:39,625 --> 00:01:40,666
Go ahead.

32
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:41,916
[grunts]

33
00:01:43,208 --> 00:01:44,625
What in the hell?!

34
00:01:44,708 --> 00:01:45,750
It is iron.

35
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:47,833
-You coulda told me that!
-I did.

36
00:01:47,916 --> 00:01:49,416
[alarm blaring]

37
00:01:51,125 --> 00:01:52,958
-Get down!
-[rapid gunfire]

38
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:24,625
[rapid gunfire]

39
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:27,875
[firing stops]

40
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,708
[whirring]

41
00:03:29,791 --> 00:03:31,333
[whirring stops]

42
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,375
We almost got turned into
Swiss cheese.

43
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:40,791
[static]

44
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:42,250
-[WOMAN over PA] Hi!
-Huh?

45
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:44,708
Zack, darling,
terribly sorry I'm late.

46
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:47,500
It was taking you two
so long to get here.

47
00:03:47,583 --> 00:03:49,333
I nearly dozed off.

48
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,958
Still,

49
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:54,458
I'm shocked you weren't killed
by those bullets.

50
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:57,250
You sure have
incredible intuition, my dear.

51
00:03:58,375 --> 00:03:59,250
Huh?

52
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,750
You know something?

53
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:04,333
I had a feeling you would
make fantastic criminals.

54
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:05,541
[moans]

55
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:07,958
I must've needed
some excitement,

56
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:10,125
because that woke me right up.

57
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,708
Yeah, well,
that's great and all,

58
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:14,166
but I don't give a shit
about your sleeping habits.

59
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,750
Enough with the chit-chat,
just let us pass.

60
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,500
I suppose I can do that.

61
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:20,791
-[applause]
-[cheering]

62
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:23,000
[WOMAN over PA]
Good job, you passed.

63
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:24,166
-[grunts]
-[cheering continues]

64
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:30,666
On this floor,

65
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,000
I'm the judge.

66
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,250
Oh! You're such terrible,
detestable sinners,

67
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:38,541
and you must atone
for all that you've done.

68
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:41,541
Luckily, you have me here.

69
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,333
I've been given the duty
and the pleasure

70
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,750
of punishing you.

71
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,833
[laughing menacingly]

72
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:53,458
I was starting to think

73
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:56,041
that annoying voice
would never shut up.

74
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:57,583
The hell does she think
she's supposed to be

75
00:04:57,666 --> 00:04:59,250
punishin' me for anyway?

76
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:01,791
We're sinners.

77
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:04,125
Ugh! Would you quit
mutterin' to yourself?

78
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,541
Let's go.

79
00:05:05,625 --> 00:05:08,625
♪

80
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:17,000
[lock clicking]

81
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,333
This is locked, too.

82
00:05:18,416 --> 00:05:19,416
Hey, you wack job,

83
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,875
I thought you were gonna
let us through!

84
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:24,250
My, you're more impatient
than I expected.

85
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:27,708
At least give me time
to finish putting on my face.

86
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:29,083
[ZACK]
What?

87
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:30,625
[WOMAN over PA]
There's a certain procedure

88
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:31,875
each criminal must go through

89
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,750
before their punishment
is assigned.

90
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:36,625
If I were you,
I'd start getting ready now.

91
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:39,208
In fact, I'll even open up
a room for you.

92
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:45,041
Every legitimate criminal
has a mugshot, right?

93
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:47,083
Take a couple
of pretty ones for me.

94
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:48,833
Oh, and it's not
a proper mugshot

95
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:50,916
without your name boards,
of course.

96
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:54,791
Ugh!

97
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:56,458
All the crap
we've had to put up with,

98
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:58,000
now we've got a photo shoot?

99
00:05:58,083 --> 00:06:00,625
This is the only way for us
to move forward.

100
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:01,791
Ugh.

101
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:04,291
Go on.

102
00:06:04,375 --> 00:06:05,208
Take it.

103
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:07,250
[groaning]

104
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,041
Argh! Fine.

105
00:06:12,125 --> 00:06:13,208
Gimme that.

106
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,166
What the hell does it say?

107
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:19,083
Isaac Foster.

108
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:20,625
Now, hurry.

109
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,125
Just hang it around your neck
and stand against the wall.

110
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:23,416
Argh.

111
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,000
All right. Goin'.

112
00:06:25,083 --> 00:06:27,000
♪

113
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,458
[ZACK grunting]

114
00:06:30,541 --> 00:06:32,750
What's takin' so long?

115
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,416
[RACHEL]
Stop moving.

116
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,208
[ZACK]
Who cares?!

117
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:37,958
It's not like
it's gotta be perfect.

118
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:39,041
It'll blur.

119
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:40,791
Are you actually
taking this seriously?

120
00:06:40,875 --> 00:06:42,083
-Hold still.
-[camera shutter clicks]

121
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:43,875
[groaning]

122
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,333
So I just push this button here?

123
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:50,083
Yep.

124
00:06:50,166 --> 00:06:52,625
But obviously, I'm quite a bit
shorter than you are,

125
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:55,208
so you'll have to adjust
the tripod before you take it.

126
00:06:55,291 --> 00:06:56,500
Be careful.

127
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,125
You can't push the button
too hard or else...

128
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,208
[camera shutter clicks]

129
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:01,541
...it'll come out...

130
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:05,000
blurry.

131
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,083
Oh, well,
we did what we had to do.

132
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:08,583
Gimme. Here, bitch!

133
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,041
Happy?

134
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:18,625
♪

135
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,416
Jeez, those drawings
really suck.

136
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,208
Mm-hmm.

137
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:26,750
[WOMAN over PA]
Hey, don't be mean.

138
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:28,166
I did the best I could.

139
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,875
They're illustrations
of the glorious punishments

140
00:07:30,958 --> 00:07:33,708
I've designed
especially for you.

141
00:07:33,791 --> 00:07:36,000
I'd like to give you a choice.

142
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:39,166
There's more than one way
to punish a sinner, you see.

143
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,875
So, I've got a variety
of painful options

144
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:43,291
waiting for you.

145
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:46,250
Of course, if you'd rather spend
the rest of your life

146
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:49,250
rotting in a cell,
that's always on the table.

147
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,750
[scoffs]

148
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:53,041
What kinda pathetic loser
would pick something like that?

149
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:55,000
[WOMAN over PA]
Aw. Too bad.

150
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:58,125
And here I was hoping
I'd get to keep you forever.

151
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,125
-[laughing]
-[belching]

152
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,166
Good point,
I'd rather die immediately.

153
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,750
[grunts]

154
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:06,458
She likes it when you say
morbid stuff like that.

155
00:08:06,541 --> 00:08:07,791
Ignore her.

156
00:08:13,375 --> 00:08:14,333
[grunts]

157
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:16,541
♪

158
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:23,041
It's a bunch of dolls.

159
00:08:23,125 --> 00:08:24,458
Why is every room
more screwed up

160
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:25,791
than the last one?

161
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,291
This one is locked, too.

162
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:34,458
What's that look for?

163
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:39,833
Aren't you going to swing at it?

164
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:40,958
What?

165
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:42,541
Those bars are made of iron.

166
00:08:42,625 --> 00:08:44,041
It won't work. Duh.

167
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:47,208
Huh?

168
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:48,958
Hey, why are you so surprised?!

169
00:08:49,041 --> 00:08:50,083
Just because I'm not smart

170
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:52,583
doesn't mean
I can't learn, okay?!

171
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:54,000
[sighs]

172
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:55,416
[clears throat]

173
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,333
You told me
you'd be useful, remember?

174
00:08:58,416 --> 00:08:59,500
You're the brains
of this outfit,

175
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,000
now figure it out.

176
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,625
I will.

177
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,500
You might as well look around
for clues, too,

178
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:05,625
while you're waiting.

179
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,958
Well, yes, ma'am, boss lady.

180
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:11,458
Hey, you better have
some kinda plan by now.

181
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:14,875
This doesn't make sense to me.

182
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:17,458
[sighs deeply]

183
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:19,750
If you can't find anything,
then I say we should bash

184
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,708
all these weird-lookin' dolls
into little pieces.

185
00:09:21,791 --> 00:09:23,541
There'd be no point.

186
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:24,750
[metal clanging]

187
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,875
Point? Seriously?

188
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:28,375
Where was that logic
when you were tryin'

189
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:31,458
to convince me to take a whack
at those iron bars, huh?

190
00:09:31,541 --> 00:09:34,291
Ugh! Argh!

191
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:36,000
Now I'm pissed off.

192
00:09:36,083 --> 00:09:38,250
This puzzle shit
is frickin' exhausting.

193
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,333
If you're tired
maybe you should sit.

194
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:43,583
Oh, yeah, you want me
to pop a squat in a doll's lap?

195
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:44,708
Don't think so.

196
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:45,708
[gasps]

197
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,541
I'll just take this spot here.

198
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:55,500
I really don't think you should
be sitting in that one--

199
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:57,041
Quit nitpickin' me.

200
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:58,583
But that chair looks like...

201
00:09:58,666 --> 00:10:00,916
Spit it out, what's the problem?

202
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,291
It's just...

203
00:10:02,375 --> 00:10:04,375
It looks a lot like
an electric chair.

204
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:07,083
[drumroll]

205
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,083
[whirring]

206
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,333
[ZACK]
What the hell?

207
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:15,250
What's the deal
with this crazy thing?

208
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,625
Don't just stand there,
do somethin'!

209
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:20,083
-[upbeat music playing]
-[ZACK grunting]

210
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,583
[WOMAN over PA]
Hi!

211
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:26,791
I've decided to join you
via this television screen.

212
00:10:27,958 --> 00:10:32,000
After all, what good's a trial
without a judge?

213
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:34,916
I'm Cathy.

214
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,875
It's about time we got to know
one another.

215
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:38,875
-[applause]
-[cheering]

216
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:44,083
My, it looks like
Zack just plopped right down

217
00:10:44,166 --> 00:10:45,458
in the electric chair.

218
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:46,375
[laughing]

219
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:49,041
Let me go, you sadistic bitch!

220
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:50,500
Oh, don't be absurd.

221
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:52,791
I'd never dream of such a thing.

222
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:53,958
What kind of judge

223
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:56,541
doesn't deal out justice
to her criminals?

224
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:59,083
[chuckles]

225
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,708
All right, then, Zack.

226
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:05,333
Let's see how much retribution
that body of yours can take.

227
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:06,875
Oh, I can't wait!

228
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:08,125
[giggles]

229
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:10,333
My heart is starting to beat
out of control.

230
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,625
-[applause]
-[cheering]

231
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:14,000
Now here we go.

232
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:15,166
Are you ready?

233
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:16,333
[music continues]

234
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:18,750
It's showtime!

235
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:21,833
-[electronic whirring]
-[groans]

236
00:11:21,916 --> 00:11:25,000
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

237
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:29,666
[screaming continues]

238
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,083
[machine powers down]

239
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:42,208
[groaning]

240
00:11:42,291 --> 00:11:43,708
[gasps]

241
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:45,958
Oh, is he dead already?

242
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:49,666
Say something.

243
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:57,500
Damn it, that hurt like hell!

244
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:58,791
Very impressive.

245
00:11:58,875 --> 00:12:00,625
Anyone else
would have been fried.

246
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,541
You really are a monster, Zack.

247
00:12:02,625 --> 00:12:04,541
That's what makes you
such an ideal criminal.

248
00:12:04,625 --> 00:12:06,833
Hey! Don't be so happy about it.

249
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:09,791
Get me off this chair
so I can kill ya!

250
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,208
Very well, then.

251
00:12:11,291 --> 00:12:13,208
If Rachel can solve
the mechanism's puzzle,

252
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:14,916
you'll be set free. [chuckles]

253
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,083
And, Zack, until she succeeds,

254
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:21,208
you are going to keep getting
zapped over and over.

255
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:24,333
But you can't.

256
00:12:24,416 --> 00:12:25,958
He'll die if this keeps up.

257
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,458
He'll be fine.

258
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:30,000
We've already seen
what a powerful monster he is.

259
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:32,708
Surely it'll take
more than that.

260
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:35,875
And besides,
doesn't it sound like fun?

261
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:37,125
Rachel.

262
00:12:38,208 --> 00:12:40,333
A sinner has no right of choice.

263
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,166
Boys and girls,

264
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:45,541
it's time for this sinner
to face his judgment.

265
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:47,500
I'd like you all
to watch closely.

266
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:49,458
You wouldn't want to miss
the satisfying sight

267
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:51,541
of this heinous criminal
writhing in agony,

268
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:52,875
now, would you?

269
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:56,083
Listen, Ray, if you're still
obsessin' over findin' a way

270
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:59,791
to make yourself useful,
now's a good time.

271
00:12:59,875 --> 00:13:01,291
Just one thing.

272
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:04,041
Whatever you gotta do
to get me out,

273
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:06,333
make sure you
save the bitch for me to kill.

274
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:07,750
[chuckles]

275
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:09,666
A criminal's value is determined

276
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,625
by the hate-filled stares
of the onlookers

277
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,958
who bear witness
to his execution.

278
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:17,833
Their eyes will bestow
sweet justice upon you.

279
00:13:17,916 --> 00:13:19,666
Good luck, Rachel.

280
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:23,041
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

281
00:13:26,541 --> 00:13:27,791
[machine powers down]

282
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:30,708
Are you still alive?

283
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:31,958
[ZACK]
Barely.

284
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:33,166
Hurry u--

285
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:36,083
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

286
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:39,041
[RACHEL] She said
the onlooker's stares

287
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:40,583
bestow justice.

288
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:45,166
Onlookers.

289
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,375
She must be talking
about the dolls.

290
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,708
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

291
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:00,666
-[machine powers down]
-[groans]

292
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,458
Can't you think any faster?

293
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:05,041
You know what it'll mean
for you if I die, dontcha?

294
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,541
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

295
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:11,166
If you die,
then you can't kill me.

296
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:12,416
That's a problem.

297
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:15,000
-[electricity crackling]
-[screaming]

298
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:20,416
I'll do my best.

299
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:23,291
[chuckles]

300
00:14:23,375 --> 00:14:25,458
Driven mad by his own regret,

301
00:14:25,541 --> 00:14:28,625
the sinner wails in pain
and begs for death.

302
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:33,333
A pitiful, hopeless display
of rage and suffering.

303
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:34,875
-[screaming]
-[CATHY] Lovely.

304
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:36,791
-[machine powers down]
-[panting]

305
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:39,916
[ZACK]
I'll kill you.

306
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,250
I'll kill you.

307
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,375
I'll kill you.

308
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,250
I'll kill you. I'll kill you.

309
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:46,708
I'll kill you. I'll kill you!

310
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:49,250
-[electricity crackling]
-[ZACK screaming]

311
00:15:04,916 --> 00:15:06,291
[grunting]

312
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:07,416
[screaming]

313
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:08,416
[grunting]

314
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:10,791
[gasps]

315
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:12,125
[machine powers down]

316
00:15:15,541 --> 00:15:18,833
Zack, if you're alive,
please say something.

317
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:29,833
Come on, Zack.

318
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,500
It's about time!

319
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:39,375
Do you have any idea
how painful that was for me?

320
00:15:41,125 --> 00:15:42,583
So you are alive.

321
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:44,458
Yeah, it sure seems that way,
doesn't it?

322
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:47,250
Thank goodness.

323
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:48,375
I don't know
what I would've done

324
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:49,333
if you had died.

325
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:50,916
[CATHY clapping]

326
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,333
You're amazing, Zack.

327
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:54,458
I can't believe
that didn't kill you.

328
00:15:54,541 --> 00:15:55,916
That stubborn will to live

329
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,208
is precisely what makes
monsters so charming.

330
00:15:58,291 --> 00:15:59,208
One sec.

331
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:00,375
Your dying moments
will be glor--

332
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:06,708
-[grunts]
-[CATHY chuckles]

333
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:08,333
What?

334
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:10,833
[CATHY over PA] Out of respect
for Rachel's hard work,

335
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:12,166
I'll let you advance.

336
00:16:13,625 --> 00:16:15,500
There's more
where that came from.

337
00:16:15,583 --> 00:16:17,958
Enough punishments
to match all your sins.

338
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:20,041
[laughing]

339
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,666
Damn, that chick's a pain.

340
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:29,791
I swear, her ass is so dead.

341
00:16:29,875 --> 00:16:31,666
Hey, let's get goin'.

342
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:36,000
What the hell?

343
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:38,750
The mechanism turned out
to be the dolls' eyes.

344
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,083
[sighs]

345
00:16:46,166 --> 00:16:47,833
I get lit up
like a Christmas tree,

346
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,833
you use my scythe on toys.

347
00:16:49,916 --> 00:16:52,208
Man, screw my life.

348
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:54,000
You were the one
who chose to sit there.

349
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:55,208
Shut up!

350
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:56,750
You didn't tell me in time!

351
00:16:58,166 --> 00:16:59,541
That room looks dangerous.

352
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:00,625
Yeah? So?

353
00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:02,125
What choice do we have?

354
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:04,750
I just think we need to be
more careful from here on out.

355
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:06,750
And I think we should
keep movin'

356
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:09,500
instead of standin' around
like a couple morons.

357
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:16,125
Hmm?

358
00:17:17,791 --> 00:17:19,208
Now we're locked in here.

359
00:17:19,291 --> 00:17:21,125
Jesus, Ray, how many more times

360
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:23,166
are you gonna be
surprised by that?

361
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,000
Ugh, this place reeks.

362
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:31,833
Nothin' in that huge safe
but this dumb piece of wire?

363
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:33,666
What a friggin' waste of space.

364
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:40,958
Hmm.

365
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,583
[metallic clang]

366
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,458
[shuddering]

367
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:47,458
Again?!

368
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:50,458
Hi. Did you miss me,
Zack, darling?

369
00:17:50,541 --> 00:17:51,875
Like the plague.

370
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:54,666
Let me give you an explanation
about this current room.

371
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,625
And you'd better listen
very carefully

372
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:58,875
if you want to escape this floor
with your life.

373
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:02,750
I got a little carried away
with the design here.

374
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:04,125
It's completely sealed,

375
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:06,375
making it impossible
for air to leak out.

376
00:18:07,375 --> 00:18:09,416
The window glass
has been reinforced,

377
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,000
so you won't be
able to break it.

378
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:12,958
And the best part,

379
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:15,791
I'm about to fill it
with something very special.

380
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:17,166
If you stay in there
long enough,

381
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:20,000
you'll be on your way
to a nice, peaceful death.

382
00:18:22,125 --> 00:18:23,166
It's poison gas.

383
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,750
-Pfft.
-[CROWD] Ah!

384
00:18:26,125 --> 00:18:28,083
Obviously, I would never
confine you two

385
00:18:28,166 --> 00:18:29,791
in a place like that
with no way out.

386
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,291
In fact, here's a gift.

387
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:34,000
I've even mercifully provided
a gas mask.

388
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:36,958
[CROWD gasps, cheers]

389
00:18:37,041 --> 00:18:38,500
As long as you do your best,

390
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,416
I've the utmost faith
you'll escape.

391
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:41,583
Oh, and of course,

392
00:18:41,666 --> 00:18:42,916
I think it'd be a bit boring

393
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,208
if I let you
sit in there forever,

394
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,041
so I've imposed a time limit.

395
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,958
I know, I'm so thorough.

396
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:50,750
After your time runs out,
you'll be given another gift.

397
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:51,875
A gas so potent,

398
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:53,750
the mask won't do
any good against it.

399
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:56,250
That's all for now.

400
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:58,791
Have yourselves a good time
in there, okay?

401
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:00,291
[alarm blaring]

402
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:02,208
[gas hissing]

403
00:19:05,583 --> 00:19:06,500
Now what?

404
00:19:06,583 --> 00:19:07,708
She said there's a way out,

405
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:09,375
so we'll just have to
solve the puzzle.

406
00:19:11,708 --> 00:19:14,041
Beats nothin', I guess.

407
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:15,875
Put the gas mask on.

408
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:17,375
You wear it. Here.

409
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:18,750
What for?

410
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:21,083
You'll pass out
a whole lot quicker than I will.

411
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:23,541
I need you to be alive
to kill me.

412
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:26,250
Plus, it'll only get in the way
while I'm searching the room.

413
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:29,375
Okay, smarty,
so what if you die?

414
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:30,291
I don't know.

415
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:31,958
[groans]

416
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:34,833
Well, without your help,
my dumb ass is toast.

417
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:35,875
So no dyin'.

418
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:43,916
Fine, then.

419
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,791
We'll trade off when it starts
getting too hard to breathe.

420
00:19:46,875 --> 00:19:48,416
Sure, but let me know.

421
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:51,583
Anyway, you got
any bright ideas, Sherlock?

422
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:54,291
There has to be a hint
in here somewhere.

423
00:19:54,375 --> 00:19:55,250
Huh?

424
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:56,791
[RACHEL]
If I had to guess...

425
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:01,250
[gasps]

426
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,625
Hmm.

427
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:05,333
[RACHEL] This corpse
is probably here for a reason.

428
00:20:06,541 --> 00:20:07,500
[gasps]

429
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,291
[RACHEL]
There's writing on the floor.

430
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:14,291
Hmm.

431
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:17,666
[ZACK] So, we just need to
move the stiff?

432
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,041
Mm-hmm.

433
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:20,791
[grunts]

434
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:23,041
[ZACK]
Well, go on, read it.

435
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:26,375
Let's see, it says,
"The one with the ugly foot,

436
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:29,958
the foolish killer, who stomped
out life with the right foot."

437
00:20:32,416 --> 00:20:35,125
It's a little hard to read,
but it says something like,

438
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:38,500
"If you feel guilty,
get rid of your right foot.

439
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:40,625
"If crime and punishment
are equivalent,

440
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:42,583
light will shine in hell."

441
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:43,750
That's it?

442
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:47,583
So we get rid
of the right foot...

443
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,458
and make the punishment
match the crime?

444
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:57,375
There's a scale.

445
00:20:57,458 --> 00:20:58,541
[coughs]

446
00:20:59,541 --> 00:21:01,750
[coughing]

447
00:21:03,416 --> 00:21:05,958
I told you to say somethin'
before it kills ya.

448
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,333
So what's our next move?

449
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,958
[RACHEL] I think we should
put that on the scale.

450
00:21:16,708 --> 00:21:19,166
Seems kinda stupid to me,
but there you go.

451
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:22,833
[RACHEL] If we balance
the weight of the crime,

452
00:21:22,916 --> 00:21:24,750
then something should happen.

453
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:38,750
I don't think that did anything.

454
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,666
[RACHEL]
No, it did.

455
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,083
Maybe.

456
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:44,166
There has to be a mechanism.

457
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:46,833
♪

458
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:52,833
[chuckles]

459
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:53,958
Hmm.

460
00:21:57,458 --> 00:21:59,125
Oh, Rachel.

461
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:00,625
Criminals always look best

462
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:02,708
when they're desperately
fighting their fate.

463
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:04,375
Suffering suits you well.

464
00:22:06,083 --> 00:22:08,041
[laughing menacingly]

465
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,000
♪

466
00:23:45,416 --> 00:23:49,875
♪

